THE fourth edition of She Can Nigeria, a movement to redesign and change the culture and perception of today’s Nigerian woman will come up this year at the Harbour Point, Victoria Island, Lagos on June 24. With the theme: She can do more, founder of the movement, Ezinne Ezeani told newsmen at a press conference early in the week at Vento Furniture showroom, Ikoyi, that  this year’s conference, which will be onsite and online, will be different and a ‘banger’ in so many ways.   Family raises the alarm over mysterious disappearance of…     Makinde, Ogun deputy governor, The Nation man, others for…     Epe, Ibadan get new estates   To start with, she said the conference is out to instill in the Nigerian woman the ‘can-do more’ spirit. “As a career woman, as a business woman, in your family, you should believe you can do more. The SheCan conference has always been known for excellence and the She Can Do More movement is to enable every woman get it into their head that they can achieve much more.” To make the conference a different and special one, Ezeani said top achieving speakers in the land such as Mrs Ibukun Awosika, Coach Lanre Olusola, Tara Fela-Durotoye, Rev Funke Felix Adejumo and several others have agreed to speak at the event. Because of the number of participants expected this year, Ezeani said the conference made a major decision to shift the venue from MUSON Centre to Habour Point. She therefore advised interested participants to register online early at SheCan Nigeria website. Additional information, she advised, could be accessed on all SheCan Social Media platforms.